-- NBA Finals on ABC Get Biggest TV Audience in 12 Years
-- Rob Golum
-- 2010-06-18T22:25:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/lakers-win-in-nba-finals-attract-largest-tv-audience-since-1998-abc-says.html

          
          
             The telecast of the Los Angeles
Lakers’ Game 7 victory for the National Basketball Association
championship attracted ABC’s largest NBA television audience
since 1998, the  Walt Disney Co.  network said.  
 The game attracted 28.2 million viewers and an 18.2 rating,
ABC said, citing preliminary results from Nielsen Co. Each
rating point equals 1 percent of the 114.9 million U.S. TV
households.  
 The Lakers’ 83-79 victory over the Boston Celtics last
night was the most-watched NBA Finals game ever for ABC, the
network said. Initial data show 40 percent of TV homes in Los
Angeles were tuned in, the network said. The game generated a 34
rating in Boston.  
 Through six games of national ratings, the finals on ABC
have averaged 16.4 million viewers.  
 Disney, based in Burbank, California, rose 8 cents to
$35.15 at 4:15 p.m. in New York Stock Exchange composite
 trading . The shares have gained 9 percent this year.  
